    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1896-10-06T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1896-10-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="596"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d596">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Olney</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Taylor</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1896-10-06">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 6, 1896</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 583.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to the Department’s No. 576 of the 24th
                    ultimo and No. 581 of the 2d instant, relating to the refusal of the
                    Governor-General of Cuba to allow the exportation of tobacco belonging to
                    certain American houses, contracts for the purchase of which had been made prior
                    to the date of his prohibitory decree, I now inclose copy of a letter<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d596fn1">Not printed.</note> from Messrs. Sutter Brothers, of
                    Chicago, whose contract with their Habana agents, Messrs. Bauriedel &amp; Co.,
                    was dated March 26 last. This may be presented with the other cases.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Richard Olney.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
